Perritt Funds, Inc. - Perritt Ultra MicroCap Fund: Private Company Information - Bloomberg









































  





















































































July 22, 2017 10:27 AM ET
Capital Markets

Company Overview of Perritt Funds, Inc. - Perritt Ultra MicroCap Fund



Snapshot People




Company Overview
Perritt Funds, Inc. - Perritt Ultra MicroCap Fund is an open-ended equity mutual fund launched and managed by Perritt Capital Management, Inc. It invests in public equity markets of the United States. The fund invests in stocks of companies operating across diversified sectors. It primarily invests in stocks of micro-cap companies with market capitalization below $300 million. The fund employs fundamental analysis with a bottom-up stock picking approach focusing on such factors such as databases and industry contacts, analyzing annual reports and financial statements, making onsite visits and meeting with top management, companies that have a high percentage of shares owned by company manage...
Perritt Funds, Inc. - Perritt Ultra MicroCap Fund is an open-ended equity mutual fund launched and managed by Perritt Capital Management, Inc. It invests in public equity markets of the United States. The fund invests in stocks of companies operating across diversified sectors. It primarily invests in stocks of micro-cap companies with market capitalization below $300 million. The fund employs fundamental analysis with a bottom-up stock picking approach focusing on such factors such as databases and industry contacts, analyzing annual reports and financial statements, making onsite visits and meeting with top management, companies that have a high percentage of shares owned by company management, relatively low levels of long-term debt, have a potential for above-average growth in revenues and/or earnings and possess reasonable valuations based on the ratios of price-to-sales, price-to-earnings, and price-to-book values, balance sheet and income statement, companies that are in a relatively early stage of development and that are undergoing corporate restructuring, initial public offerings, companies believed to possess undervalued assets and unseasoned companies to create its portfolio. It benchmarks the performance of its portfolio against the Russell Microcap Index and the Russell 2000 Index. The fund employs proprietary research to create its portfolio. It was formerly known as Peritt Funds, Inc. - Perritt Emerging Opportunities Fund. Perritt Funds, Inc. - Perritt Ultra MicroCap Fund was formed on August 27, 2004 and is domiciled in the United States.
Detailed Description


