Perritt Funds, Inc. - Perritt MicroCap Opportunities Fund: Private Company Information - Bloomberg









































  





















































































July 22, 2017 10:27 AM ET
Capital Markets

Company Overview of Perritt Funds, Inc. - Perritt MicroCap Opportunities Fund



Snapshot People




Company Overview
Perritt Funds, Inc. - Perritt MicroCap Opportunities Fund is an open-ended equity mutual fund launched and managed by Perritt Capital Management, Inc. It invests in public equity markets of the United States. The fund invests in stocks of companies operating across diversified sectors. It primarily invests in value and growth stocks of micro-cap companies having a market capitalization below $500 million. The fund employs fundamental analysis with bottom-up stock picking approach focusing on factors such as balance sheet and income statement, companies that have demonstrated above-average growth in revenues and/or earnings, have a high percentage of their shares owned by company management, ...
Perritt Funds, Inc. - Perritt MicroCap Opportunities Fund is an open-ended equity mutual fund launched and managed by Perritt Capital Management, Inc. It invests in public equity markets of the United States. The fund invests in stocks of companies operating across diversified sectors. It primarily invests in value and growth stocks of micro-cap companies having a market capitalization below $500 million. The fund employs fundamental analysis with bottom-up stock picking approach focusing on factors such as balance sheet and income statement, companies that have demonstrated above-average growth in revenues and/or earnings, have a high percentage of their shares owned by company management, possess modest price-to-sales ratios and price-to-earnings ratios that are below their long-term annual growth rate, and possess relatively low levels of long-term debt, special situations such as companies that possess valuable patents, companies undergoing restructuring, and companies involved in large share repurchase programs to create its portfolio. It benchmarks the performance of its portfolio against the Russell 2000 Index and the Russell Microcap Index. The fund employs proprietary research to create its portfolio. It was formerly known as Perritt MicroCap Opportunities Fund, Inc. - Perritt MicroCap Opportunities Fund. Perritt Funds, Inc. - Perritt MicroCap Opportunities Fund was formed on April 11, 1988 and is domiciled in the United States.
Detailed Description


